[src:guava-java-lib/immutable-object] In the language of guarantees, mutable has no guarantees (the function might change the object), `const` is an outward-only guarantee that the function will not change anything, and `immutable` is a bidirectional guarantee (the function will not change the value and the caller must not change it).
